      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:63:25",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ أَمِيرَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) أُتِيَ بِرَجُلٍ عَبِثَ بِذَكَرِهِ فَضَرَبَ يَدَهُ حَتَّى احْمَرَّتْ ثُمَّ زَوَّجَهُ مِنْ بَيْتِ الْمَالِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Sinan, from Talha Bin Zayd, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said that they came with a man to Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup>, who had tampered with his manhood. So he<sup>asws</sup> hit his hand until it was red. Then he<sup>asws</sup> got him married from the public treasury’."
        ]
      }
    }
